Enum is a reference datatype in Java which is used to define a fixed set of constants. 

enum SIZE {
  LARGE, 
  MEDIUM,
  SMALL
}


class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        SIZE size = SIZE.MEDIUM;
        
        switch(size) {
            case LARGE: System.out.println("large");
                        break;
            case MEDIUM: System.out.println("medium");
                        break;
            case SMALL: System.out.println("small");
                        break;
        }
        
        for(SIZE sizee: SIZE.values()) {
            System.out.println(sizee);
        }
    }
}


- Enums can have fields, constructors and methods.
- prevents invalid values from being assigned
- enum constants are public, static and final
